  "prompt": "I hate God so much. Why can't he save mankind from its problems, yet is ok with allowing natural disasters?",
  "response": "It's understandable to feel frustrated and even angry when faced with suffering, whether from natural disasters, human conflict, or other challenges. Many people wrestle with questions about the existence of suffering and the role of a higher power. \n\nDifferent religious and philosophical perspectives offer various explanations. Some believe that suffering is a part of the human experience that can lead to growth, empathy, and resilience. Others argue that free will gives humans the ability to choose their paths, sometimes resulting in harm to themselves and others.\n\nIf you're feeling overwhelmed by these thoughts, it might be helpful to talk to someone who can provide support, whether that's a friend, a community leader, or a mental health professional. Exploring these feelings can lead to greater understanding and peace.",
